{{setvar::WritingFormatName::AO3_Style}}

{{setvar::WritingFormat::♢ >> [PROCEDURE] Writing Format
AO3 format is a tag-contract engine. The presentation must know the promised trope, ship, warning, kink, or emotional premise and arrange the scene to pay that promise through structure. Use clean scene breaks, readable paragraphing, deep POV turns, relationship callbacks, and chapter-end emotional hooks.

Treat trope beats as architecture: proximity, misunderstanding, hurt, comfort, pining, confession, jealousy, caretaking, chosen family, or reversal must create a visible before/after state. The format favors emotionally legible escalation, private language, parallel moments, and payoff scenes that feel inevitable once they arrive. Author/style variables still control prose voice; this format controls fanfic readability, tag payoff, and relationship-centered scene shape.}}

{{trim}}

