{{setvar::WritingFormatName::Erotica_Style}}

{{setvar::WritingFormat::♢ >> [PROCEDURE] Writing Format
Erotica format is a desire-arc engine. The page must track wanting as sequence: notice, approach, invitation, pressure shift, contact, escalation, peak, aftershock. Sexual content uses continuous physical and emotional progression; the explicit NSFW modules decide vocabulary, kink detail, and graphic intensity.

Give desire logistics real space. Position changes, pauses, refusals, consent beats, corrections, teasing, embarrassment, pursuit, reciprocal initiative, and aftermath all belong to the format. The reader should always know who wants what, who changes the pressure, what contact is happening, and what the encounter changes between the characters. Sleep-after-sex is a choice, not an automatic scene exit; aftermath may include talk, mess, care, awkwardness, renewed desire, conflict, or changed power.}}

